<subSubSection box="[264,1276,1584,1650]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1276,1584,1650]" box="[264,407,1584,1609]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis box="[264,407,1584,1609]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1276,1584,1650]" box="[312,1276,1624,1650]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
North Island in Hawkes Bay and along east coast in the Gisborne region (
<figureCitation box="[1174,1262,1624,1650]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="16.[264,367,1331,1355]" captionTargetBox="[323,1268,300,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[306,1282,283,1327]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 24. Known distribution of: Z. angustifasciatum; Z. batesi; Z. dugdalei; Z. kaikouraiensis; Z. minutum; Z. nonmaculatum; Z. taranakiensis; Z. opacum. The Z. batesi record on Kermadec Island is not shown here. (Map with permission from Ian Henderson, Massey University)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170230/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1229,1262,1624,1650]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,1704,1890]" box="[264,387,1704,1729]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis box="[264,387,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,1704,1890]" lastBlockId="32.[264,1323,284,390]" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
The 
<typeStatus box="[371,473,1744,1770]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">holotype</typeStatus>
is badly damaged; the colour is clearly visible but the specimen is covered in dust. The right elytron is damaged, the wings are separated from the body and the abdomen is missing. Segments 
<number box="[675,732,1824,1850]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="7.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="4.0">4–11</number>
of left antennae are missing, and the hind legs and body are attached to the pin by glue. The species name 
<taxonomicName box="[995,1138,1864,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Obrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabricianum">
<emphasis box="[995,1138,1864,1889]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">fabricianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood" box="[264,475,284,310]" pageId="32" pageNumber="42" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1845) Longicorn Coleoptera of New Zealand. Species XV: Arcana Entomologica, 2, pp. 25 - 28." type="journal article" year="1845">
Westwood (
<number box="[405,466,284,310]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="1845.0">1845</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" box="[814,1029,284,310]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Clytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[814,907,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">minutus</emphasis>
Fabricius
</taxonomicName>
, which he regarded as a name preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName box="[528,668,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Zorion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutum">
<emphasis box="[528,668,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">O. minutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is not known however, what this 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1251,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Zorion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutum">
<emphasis box="[1111,1251,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">O. minutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is (S. Shute, 
<collectionCode box="[345,436,364,390]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">BMNH</collectionCode>
, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
